timeline.bodyText: @JimSuplizio @praveenkuttappan something in this automation looks wrong can you guys take a look?
timeline.author: weshaggard

replies.bodyText:
@weshaggard and @praveenkuttappan, the automation isn't wrong, the CHANGELOG is. We saw some similar issues with badly formatted CHANGELOGs this release. The reason why you're seeing 3 entries is because of "4.2.0-beta.2 (2020-04-09)" is actually incorrect, it should have been 4.1.0-beta.2 (2020-04-09). The reason you're seeing 3 entries is because each commit added a 'missing' entry based upon what was in their respective version files at the time.
@g2vinay manually updated this version as part of #9758 which, unfortunately, wasn't the correct version.
replies.author: JimSuplizio

timeline.message:
Update CHANGELOG.md

Fix the changelog which had an incorrect version for the release that happened today. The version released was 4.1.0-beta.2, not 4.2.0-beta.2
